div.p:



                  § 27
Thus in ſome Latine fragments of Polycarpus's Epiſtle ſpeaking of Valens a Presbyter of Philippi, and his having committed ſomewhat utterly unworthy of that calling (which is not there named, and perhaps by that may be rather gueſſed at what it was) by his example he admoniſheth others to abſtain [ab avaritia] (that ſure was in Greek, 
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) from inordinate deſires, [& ſint casti] and be chast. Adding, that whoſoever did not thus abſtain [
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ] ab idololatria coinquinabitur, & tanquam inter Gentes judicabitur, will be contaminated by Idolatry, and ſhall be judged as among the Gentiles.
